my/ The Chinese Nationalist Army, ww2-weapons.com] Retrieved 11 March 2016</ref>\n** 2,600,000 (1939)<ref name=\"Hsiung 171\">Hsiung, ''China's Bitter Victory'', p. 171</ref>\n** 5,700,000 (1945)<ref name=\"Horner2003\">{{cite book|author=David Murray Horner|title=The Second World War: The Pacific|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DShPzguQ64UC&pg=PA14|accessdate=March 6, 2011|date=July 24, 2003|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-0-415-96845-4|pages=14\u201315}}</ref>\n* {{flagicon image|Flag of the Chinese Communist Party (Pre-1996).svg}} '''Chinese Communists''':\n** 40,000 (1937)<ref name=\"China's Bitter Victory\">{{cite book | language = en | author = Hsiung | title = China's Bitter Victory | url =  | date = 1992 | location =  | publisher = Routledge | id =  | isbn = 978-1563242465 | pages = 79 }}</ref>\n** 166,700 (1938)<ref name=\"\u516b\u8def\u519b\u00b7\u8868\u518c\">{{cite book | author = \u4e2d\u56fd\u4eba\u6c11\u89e3\u653e\u519b\u5386\u53f2\u8d44\u6599\u4e1b\u4e66\u7f16\u5ba1\u59d4\u5458\u4f1a | script-title=zh:\u516b\u8def\u519b\u00b7\u8868\u518c | url =  | date = 1994 | location =  | publisher = \u89e3\u653e\u519b\u51fa\u7248\u793e | id =  | isbn = 978-7-5065-2290-8 | pages = \u7b2c3\u9875 | language = zh }}</ref>\n** 488,744 (1940)<ref>\u4e01\u661f\uff0c\u300a\u65b0\u56db\u519b\u521d\u671f\u7684\u56db\u4e2a\u652f\u961f\u2014\u2014\u65b0\u56db\u519b\u7ec4\u7ec7\u6cbf\u9769\u7b80\u4ecb(2)\u300b\u3010J\u3011\uff0c\u94c1\u519b\uff0c2007\u5e74\u7b2c2\u671f\uff0c38\u201340\u9875</ref>\n** 1,200,000 (1945)<ref name=\"Hsiung\">{{cite book |title = China's Bitter Victory: The War With Japan, 1937\u20131945 |url = https://books.google.com/?id=3Yt6TTRdUzwC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false |publisher = M.E. Sharpe publishing |author = Hsiung, James C. |year = 1992 |location = New York |isbn = 1-56324-246-X}}</ref>}}\n| strength2 = {{plainlist|\n* {{Flagdeco|Empire of Japan|army|size=23px}} '''Japanese''':\n** 600,000 (1937)<ref>{{cite book|last1=Black|